Natalia María Pacheco-Tallaj

I am a doctoral candidate in Mathematics at MIT. Before that, I was an undergraduate at Harvard until 2020 and a Fulbright Fellow at the University of Copenhagen until 2021.

I study the homotopical and algebraic-geometric aspects of problems in quantum matter and supersymmetric field theory. I am also interested in applied geometry, specifically to problems in computer graphics and physics simulation. I have worked at the Adobe 3D Graphics and Interactive Design Lab for the past 2 summers.

I am from San Juan, Puerto Rico.
